fields.name: The Half-full Mug
fields.desc: You enter a lively and crowded tavern. There is a door to the North and West

fields.name: The Manaa Waste
fields.desc: Once a vibrant magical city, the remnants of the wasted realm stand as a warning to others. A cliff blocks any travel to the West.

fields.name: The Spire of Lightning
fields.desc: A place as dangerous as it is magical. Enter at your own risk.

fields.name: The Land of Poison Tears
fields.desc: A millenia of mining by the stone dwarves have rendered this land ill, and poison accompanies rain from the skies. Make haste: your only way out is due East.

fields.name: The Wyvern Hills
fields.desc: Flying lions - what could go wrong?

fields.name: The Sea of Thene
fields.desc: Dark seas stretch the horizon from North to South - the currently known edge of the world

fields.name: The Pit of Eternal Night
fields.desc: You are in a dark warren of caves. It's not really eternally night, but it's dark so we don't quibble.
fields.EAST: The Citadel of the Lich Queen

fields.name: The Twilight Vale
fields.desc: You are in a forest of massive purple trees that cast an amethyst glow. It is very quiet, but you feel as though someone is watching you.

fields.name: The Black Gauntlet of Sorrows
fields.desc: A dark hallway stretches east, paintings of destruction reaching up beyond sight.
fields.EAST: The Tower of Ulfang the Black

fields.name: The Citadel of the Lich Queen
fields.desc: No, she is of no relation to Arthas, thank you very much, and kindly asks you to leave.
